		"name": "Task Manager API",
		"description": "This collection contains all API endpoints for the **Task Manager** project built with **Node.js, Express, and MongoDB Atlas**.  \n  \nIt demonstrates a complete CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operation flow with proper separation of concerns using controllers, models, and routes.\n\nThe API allows you to:\n\n1. **Create** a new task and store it in MongoDB.\n    \n2. **Retrieve** all existing tasks.\n    \n3. **Retrieve** a single task by its unique ID.\n    \n4. **Update** an existing task.\n    \n5. **Delete** a task permanently from the database.\n    \n\nEach request returns JSON responses with appropriate HTTP status codes.  \n  \nEnsure that your server is running locally (e.g., `http://localhost:5000`) and your MongoDB Atlas connection is active before testing.\n\nEndFragment",
